author: @Paraense_Anonimo
text:
*"Tally" do BLACKPINK é um hino de empoderamento que fala sobre ser você mesmo e viver a vida do seu jeito, sem se importar com o que os outros pensam. A música incentiva a ignorar as expectativas da sociedade e a abraçar a independência. O refrão destaca que ninguém deve controlar o que você faz, reforçando a ideia de assumir a responsabilidade pela própria vida e buscar o que realmente deseja. No final, "Tally" motiva as pessoas a serem corajosas e autênticas na busca pela vida que querem viver.*

Meu recado: eu dedico essa música para alguns dos vizinhos fofoqueiros aqui da rua que adoram reparar na vida dos outros! 😅

text: The lyrics of all the songs on the Born Pink album are so meaningful. This song proves that. After the ballads, they switch back to their hard images.They show everyone how strong they are. It's nice that group members who talk about themselves as they are are transparent. author: @mehlanie13
text:
i enjoy this song so much, partly because of the meaningful lyrics.  
- i think "I do what I want with who I like", "Everybody tells me to play nice", "Sometimes I like to go play dirty/Just like all of the ** boys do", "I’ll just do it like the boys say/I’m gettin’ mine, gettin’ mine", and "But my body don’t belong to nah-uh-uh none of them though" are lines that debunk toxic views about women. women have always been told to act all nice and innocent to attract men, or behave "loyally" to men. but the truth is that women should be allowed to engage in and break out of any relationships as they wish because they know what's best for them, not men. as blackpink says, "That’s my choice and there’s no one I’m hurting", so why don't we let women have free will without criticizing them all the time for wanting to have worthwhile relationships?
- and of course, "no one’s keeping tally", nobody really cares what you're doing. blackpink convinces us to be ourselves and refrain from agonizing ourselves with people's judgements, and i think that's a mindset that everybody needs to own.
